The Reserve Bank of India has permitted Indian banks to transact in the Euro, the new currency unit of the European Monetary Union.
In a circular issued to banks, RBI permitted banks to trade and invoice in the Euro, freely convert legacy EMU currencies into the Euro, and accept Euro-denominated bank deposits and remittances.
